    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-03-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-03-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="551" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d551">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Williams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 18.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-03-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 6, 1868.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your dispatch No. 17, of February 6, has
                            been received, and is exceedingly interesting.</p>
                <p>The extracts from the President’s message to congress, and the report of
                            the minister of foreign relations and public instructions accompanying
                            it, exhibit the progressive condition of that republic, and furnish <pb facs="0985" n="925" xml:id="pg_925"/> gratifying proofs of the
                            earnest disposition of the government to improve the material, moral,
                            and educational advancement of its people.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alpheus S. Williams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
